layer_names = {'mfccs': 'MFCCs',
               'layer_1': 'Dense layer 1',
               'layer_2': 'Dense layer 2',
               'layer_3': 'Dense layer 3',
               'rnn_output': 'LSTM',
               'layer_5': 'Dense layer 4',
               'layer_6': 'Raw logits'}

def array_to_webm(array, title, path):
    for filename in os.listdir('temp_png'):
        os.remove('temp_png/' + filename)
    for i, a in zip(range(len(array)), array):
        size = 6
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(size, size), dpi=100)
        im = ax.imshow(np.swapaxes(a, 0, 1),
                       aspect='auto',
                       interpolation='nearest',
                       cmap='coolwarm',
                       vmin=array.min(),
                       vmax=array.max())
        fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax, orientation='vertical')
        ax.set_xlabel('Time window')
        ax.set_ylabel('Neuron')
        ax.set_title(title)
        # plt.show()
        # return
        plt.savefig('temp_png/%.5d.png' % i)
        plt.close()
    subprocess.call(['ffmpeg', '-y', '-i', 'temp_png/%05d.png', '-vf', 'fps=24', path])

def display_anim(name):
    anim = pickle.load(open('%s.pickle' % name, 'rb'))
    for key in layer_names.keys():#anim.keys():
        print('Creating .webm for ' + key)
        array_to_webm(anim[key], layer_names[key], key + '.webm')
        display(Video(key + '.webm', embed=True, html_attributes='autoplay controls loop'))
        # break
# array_to_webm(np.random.randn(24, 10, 12), 'output.webm')
